text.section:
If a lessor fails to deliver the goods in conformity to the lease contract (KRS 355.2A-509) or repudiates the lease contract (KRS 355.2A-402), or a lessee rightfully rejects the goods (KRS 355.2A-509) or justifiably revokes acceptance of the goods (KRS 355.2A-517), then with respect to any goods involved, and with respect to all of the goods if under an installment lease contract the value of the whole lease contract is substantially impaired (KRS 355.2A-510), the lessor is in default under the lease contract and the lessee may:
Cancel the lease contract (subsection (1) of KRS 355.2A-505);
Recover so much of the rent and security as has been paid and is just under the circumstances;
Cover and recover damages as to all goods affected whether or not they have been identified to the lease contract (KRS 355.2A-518 and 355.2A-520), or recover damages for nondelivery (KRS 355.2A-519 and 355.2A-520);
Exercise any other rights or pursue any other remedies provided in the lease contract.
